external_knowledge:
- Hierarchy level refers to the position of a faculty member in the organizational structure, with level 1 representing the topmost position; 
- The highest qualification of a faculty member is the highest academic degree they have obtained; 
- The area of specialization is the specific field in which a faculty member has expertise; 
- The date of joining is the date when a faculty member started working at the institution; 
- Employment type refers to whether a faculty member is employed full-time, part-time, or on contract.

sql:
SELECT name, highest_qualification
FROM faculties
ORDER BY name ASC;

SELECT employment_type, COUNT(*) AS faculty_count
FROM faculties
GROUP BY employment_type;

SELECT name
FROM faculties
WHERE highest_qualification = (SELECT MAX(highest_qualification) FROM faculties);
